1
00:00:05,156 --> 00:00:06,495
The devotees ...

2
00:00:06,495 --> 00:00:08,465
We see different ślokas,

3
00:00:08,465 --> 00:00:11,125
the Sarvabhauma śloka,
and elsewhere they say,

4
00:00:11,125 --> 00:00:13,405
they don’t care 
if people think they are mad.

5
00:00:13,405 --> 00:00:14,826
Also Madhavendra Puri

6
00:00:14,826 --> 00:00:17,876
[Who is Crazy?]

7
00:00:17,926 --> 00:00:21,811
saying, “Let people say 
I’ve lost my mind,

8
00:00:21,811 --> 00:00:25,191
let the Vedic people say this, 
the ordinary people that,

9
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:27,061
my relatives disown me”,—

10
00:00:27,061 --> 00:00:28,531
he goes through a whole list

11
00:00:28,531 --> 00:00:33,531
of all the people who are
generally taken to matter.

12
00:00:33,531 --> 00:00:36,843
Put it that way, people 
who are generally taken to matter,

13
00:00:36,843 --> 00:00:39,843
that their opinions matter.

14
00:00:39,843 --> 00:00:44,055
He is saying, “Let them all 
go to hell”.

15
00:00:44,064 --> 00:00:45,279
And he said,

16
00:00:45,279 --> 00:00:51,999
аnd he said, “And you can add to this, 
that they can say,

17
00:00:51,999 --> 00:00:57,209
that this Krisna consciousness you seek,
by your own admission, you don’t have it.

18
00:00:57,209 --> 00:00:58,779
Add that!

19
00:00:58,779 --> 00:01:02,159
So not only have I lost my mind, 
I am delusional and like ...

20
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:04,889
But add to that, the very thing 
that I aspire to,

21
00:01:04,889 --> 00:01:07,889
by my own admission—
I don’t have it.”

22
00:01:07,889 --> 00:01:13,086
He said, “But I’m still, not gonna budge 
an inch from pursuing this.”

23
00:01:13,086 --> 00:01:18,316
It’s a very beautiful verse 
attributed to Madhavendra Puri.

24
00:01:20,020 --> 00:01:23,720
There’s a saying that’s made it’s way 
around the Internet,

25
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:26,140
no one is really sure who said it.

26
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:29,410
But it goes something like this, 
it’s saying,

27
00:01:29,410 --> 00:01:35,810
“And they were thought to be mad, 
who were dancing,

28
00:01:35,810 --> 00:01:39,750
by those who could not hear the music.”

29
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:46,170
That reminds us 
of Krisna consciousness,

30
00:01:46,170 --> 00:01:49,805
yā niśā sarva-bhūtānāṁ 
[Bg: 2.69]

31
00:01:49,805 --> 00:01:53,440
āmi—eka bātula, tumi—dvitīya 
[Cc: Madhya, 8.291]

32
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:57,075
“I am crazy the first, 
you are crazy the second”—

33
00:01:57,075 --> 00:02:00,015
Mahaprabhu to Ramananda.

34
00:02:01,525 --> 00:02:04,827
So when we say ‘madness’ ...

35
00:02:06,497 --> 00:02:11,409
What’s madness?... To ... 
in the world ...

36
00:02:11,409 --> 00:02:15,981
Krisna consciousness is like madness 
to people.

37
00:02:17,744 --> 00:02:22,025
But for those who are Krisna conscious,

38
00:02:22,025 --> 00:02:28,565
the ... people of this world, 
they think they’re mad.

39
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:29,898
Like Guru Maharaj says,

40
00:02:29,898 --> 00:02:33,028
“Freedom for the senses, 
freedom from the senses—

41
00:02:33,028 --> 00:02:35,868
what is freedom?”

42
00:02:35,868 --> 00:02:39,488
When you are free from the influence 
of the mind and senses,

43
00:02:39,488 --> 00:02:44,968
then you could say you are going 
in the right direction.

44
00:02:44,968 --> 00:02:49,139
But just like that man on the chariot 
with the five wild horses—

45
00:02:49,139 --> 00:02:51,409
that’s not freedom.

46
00:02:51,409 --> 00:02:56,879
Saying, “No, the car, the chariot 
is going all over the place, freely!”

47
00:02:56,879 --> 00:02:59,692
No, you have been dragged around.

48
00:02:59,692 --> 00:03:02,692
Humiliated. 
The soul is being humiliated.

49
00:03:02,692 --> 00:03:11,852
So even if someone is crazy, 
in a conventional, stereotypical sense,

50
00:03:11,971 --> 00:03:19,421
If they’re ... they like to do some service
or something ... It’s all right.

51
00:03:19,513 --> 00:03:23,950
Once I was in Moscow 
at Avtozavodskaya, our old ...

52
00:03:23,950 --> 00:03:26,794
And someone said,

53
00:03:28,754 --> 00:03:35,458
“Can ... If someone is an idiot, 
can they be Krisna conscious?”

54
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:38,103
This is a Russian question.

55
00:03:39,456 --> 00:03:41,976
And I said, “Yes”.

56
00:03:42,436 --> 00:03:45,129
And then Muralishwar, 
actually he was translating ...

57
00:03:45,129 --> 00:03:48,402
Then the man said the question,
but on another level.

58
00:03:48,402 --> 00:03:53,876
He said, “But what if someone 
is a complete, total idiot?”

59
00:03:55,966 --> 00:03:59,509
And I said, “I can assure you.”

60
00:03:59,722 --> 00:04:02,912
[Laughing]

61
00:04:05,228 --> 00:04:10,498
The first devotee, who shaved his head 
and wore robes,

62
00:04:10,498 --> 00:04:13,498
got arrested in New York.

63
00:04:13,498 --> 00:04:20,670
Taken to Bellevue which is the name 
of the hospital there for crazy people.

64
00:04:21,644 --> 00:04:26,864
They thought he was ... 
you know, had lost his mind.

65
00:04:27,564 --> 00:04:32,974
And so, Srila Prabhupada wrote 
a pamphlet in response to this.

66
00:04:33,221 --> 00:04:35,613
He wrote a letter to the hospital,

67
00:04:35,613 --> 00:04:37,777
about what Krisna consiousness is,

68
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,561
the Krisna consciousness movement,
other things.

69
00:04:39,561 --> 00:04:44,357
But the title of the pamphlet was
“Who is crazy?”

70
00:04:45,916 --> 00:04:48,646
And then he expressed 
so many things.

